Three A's or AAA
Arrange - Define's the testing environment & values
Act - Run the actual code / function that should be tested
Assert - Evaluate the produced value / result and compare it to the expected value / result
Only test Your code e.g. Fetch()API

1. Don't test if it works as intended
2. Don't test your server-side code implicitly via your client-side code
3. Write separate tests for your backend code instead
   Do Test your client-side reaction to different responses & errors

Rules in writing Good tests

1. Arrange-Act-Assert
2. Only test one thing
3. Focus on the essence of a test when arranging
4. Keep your number of assertions("expects")low
